.TH "snd_ac97_update" 9 "snd_ac97_update" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_ac97_update \- update the value on the given register
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_ac97_update
.BI "(struct snd_ac97 *ac97 "  ","
.BI "unsigned short reg "  ","
.BI "unsigned short value "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ac97" 12
the ac97 instance
.IP "reg" 12
the register to change
.IP "value" 12
the value to set
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Compares the value with the register cache and updates the value
only when the value is changed.
.SH "RETURN"
1 if the value is changed, 0 if no change, or a negative
code on failure.
